                            District 2:  Doug Coward
                                                  [green_white_right.gif]



   Commissioner Doug Coward has been in Florida since 1984 and moved to
   St. Lucie County in 1991. He graduated from the Florida State
   University with a masters degree in urban and regional planning and a
   dual bachelors degree in the social sciences and geography. He has also
   worked as a professional planner for St. Lucie County, 1000 Friends of
   Florida, and the private sector. His wife Tara has completed her
   studies in Ultrasound.

   Commissioner Coward (Dem.) was sworn into office on November 17, 1998.
   He serves as the Chairman of the Board of County Commissioners and the
   Tourist Development Council. He is a member of the St. Lucie County
   Fire District Board, the Treasure Coast Regional Planning Council, the
   Council of Local Stormwater Management for the St. Lucie River and
   Indian River Lagoon, Heathy Kids of St. Lucie County, the St. Lucie
   County Chamber of Commerce Board of Directors, the Florida Regional
   Council Association, the Treasure Coast Community Alliance and the
   Shared Services Network Executive Round Table.
